Course data for 98,000 undergraduates

Source: R/midfieldcourses.R
midfieldcourses.Rd

Data frame of course attributes of 97,064 undergraduates with 3.5 M observations and 12 academic course variables keyed by student ID, term, and course. Each observation is one course in one term for one student. A stratified sample of the MIDFIELD database.

midfieldcourses

Format

data.table with 3.5 M observations and 12 variables, occupying 348 MB of memory. Each observation is one course in one term for one student. The variables are:

id

character, unique anonymized MIDFIELD student identifier

institution

character, anonymized institution name

term_course

numeric, academic year and term the course is taken, format YYYYT

course

character, course name

abbrev

character, course alpha identifier (e.g. ENGR, MATH, ENGL)

number

character, course numeric identifier (e.g. 101, 3429)

section

character, course section identifier

hours_course

numeric, number of credit-hours for successful course completion

type

character, predominant delivery method for this section

pass_fail

character, whether or not the course was offered on a pass/fail basis

grade

character, course grade

faculty_rank

academic rank of the person teaching the course

Source

Data provided by the MIDFIELD project: https://engineering.purdue.edu/MIDFIELD

Examples

midfieldcourses
